# AKS Cluster Auto Scaler 

## Configure Autoscaler 
[Cluster autoscaler docs](https://github.com/MicrosoftDocs/azure-docs/blob/main/articles/aks/cluster-autoscaler.md#using-the-autoscaler-profile)

[Cluster autoscaler docs #2](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/aks/cluster-autoscaler)


update autoscaler to scale down after 1 minute (instead of 10) and scale up after 1 minutes (instead of 10)

```bash
az aks update -g workshop -n aksworkshop \      --cluster-autoscaler-profile \ 
scale-down-delay-after-add=1m \ 
scale-down-unneeded-time=1m \ 

```
>NOTE: for demo purposes only, in a production environment the best practice is to use the default 10 minute delay

deploy application 
```bash
kubectl apply -f testdeploy.yaml
```

